{{Infobox language |name=Lavu |altname=Talu |nativename= |region=[[Yunnan]] |states=China |ethnicity=[[Yi people|Yi]] |speakers={{sigfig|13600|2}} |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Lisoish languages|Lisoish]] |fam6=Lalo–Lavu<ref>Lama, Ziwo Qiu-Fuyuan (2012:145), ''Subgrouping of Nisoic (Yi) Languages'', thesis, University of Texas at Arlington</ref> |fam7=Lavu–Kuansi |dia1=Lang'e |iso3=yta |lc1=yne|ld1=Lang'e |glotto=talu1238 |glottorefname=Talu }}
'''Lavu''' ({{zh|拉乌}}; autonym: ''{{IPA|lɑ˥vu̠˥}}'') is a [[Loloish language]] of [[Yongsheng County]], [[Yunnan]], China.
Languages related to Lavu include Liude 六得, Nazha 纳渣, and perhaps Shuitian 水田, Zhili 支里, Luo 倮, Ziyi 子彝, and Liming 黎明.
