{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Pakistanis in Brunei | image = | population = 500 (2005)<ref>[http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf Yearbook 2004-2005, Ministry of Labour, Manpower & Overseas Pakistanis] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100524170403/http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf |date=2010-05-24 }}</ref> | popplace = | langs = [[Urdu]], [[English language|English]], [[Malay language|Malay]] | rels = [[Islam]] | related = [[Pakistani diaspora]] }}
Up to 450 [[Pakistanis]] work in [[Brunei]],<ref>[http://www.bt.com.bn/home_news/2009/05/07/pakistan_navy_men_visit_bt Pakistan navy men visit BT]</ref> of these there are around 70 Pakistani medical doctors working in various healthcare departments of Brunei.<ref>Reehan Sabri, "Working in Brunei Darussalam," in Pakistan Journal of Medical Sciences, Oct-Dec 2007, Vol 23, No 5, 814-817.</ref> Adding up the spouses and children of these Pakistani workers in Brunei, makes up the total population of Pakistanis in Brunei to be about 1500.<ref>[http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf Yearbook 2004-2005, Ministry of Labour, Manpower & Overseas Pakistanis] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100524170403/http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf |date=2010-05-24 }}</ref>
