{{Infobox website | name = Wireless Philosophy | logo = File:Wireless Philosophy logo.png | logocaption = | screenshot = | collapsible = | collapsetext = | caption = | url = {{URL|http://www.wi-phi.com}} | editor = | based_in = | slogan = | commercial = | type = Educational video website | registration = | language = English | num_users = | content_license = | owner = | author = | launch_date = {{nowrap|{{start date and years ago|mf=yes|2013|6|7}}}} | alexa = | revenue = | current_status = Online | footnotes = }}
'''Wireless Philosophy''' or '''Wi-Phi''' is an [[open-access]] [[philosophy]] website that aims to "introduce people to the practice of philosophy by making videos that are freely available in a form that is entertaining".<ref>[http://www.wi-phi.com/about-us/mission-statement Mission Statement]</ref><ref>[http://dailynous.com/2015/01/17/lupe-fiasco-hands-off-philosophy-sunday-to-wiphi/ Lupe Fiasco Hands Off Philosophy Sunday to WiPhi]</ref><ref>[https://www.khanacademy.org/partner-content/wi-phi Wi-Phi]</ref><ref>[http://www.openculture.com/2013/06/introducing_wireless_philosophy.html Introducing Wireless Philosophy: An Open Access Philosophy Project Created by Yale and MIT]</ref><ref>[http://www.indyweek.com/indyweek/dukes-paul-henne-gives-philosophy-to-the-masses-in-bite-sized-animated-videos/Content?oid=4294622 Duke's Paul Henne gives philosophy to the masses in bite-sized animated videos]</ref><ref>[http://nhseb.unc.edu/for-teams/general-questions/ Ethical and Moral Theories]</ref><ref>[https://philosophynow.org/links/Philosophy_Videos Philosophy Videos]</ref> Its founder and executive director is [[Gaurav Vazirani]], a PhD student at [[Yale University]]. According to [[Mel Thompson]], Wireless Philosophy is "a very good online resource for those coming new to philosophy, and for students from GCSE upwards."<ref>[http://www.mel-thompson.co.uk/Blogs.htm Philosophy and Ethics]</ref>
